obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (78363)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78363&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Maritime`
  line `Anti-Piracy Act, 2022.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act shall apply to the high seas.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 22nd day of February, 2023, vide notification No. S.O. 802(E), dated 22nd February, 2023, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (78364)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78364&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "authorised personnel" means the officers and sailors assigned to warships or military aircraft`
  line `of the Indian Navy or officers and enrolled persons of the Coast Guard assigned to ships or aircraft of`
  line `the Indian Coast Guard or officers of the Central Government or the State Government authorised for`
  line `any ship or aircraft clearly marked and identifiable as being on Government service;`
  line
  line `(b) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(c) "Convention" means the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea, 1982;`
  line
  line `(d) "Designated Court" means a Court of Session specified as such under section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) "high seas" includes the Exclusive Economic Zone and all waters beyond the jurisdiction of any`
  line `other State.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "Exclusive Economic Zone" means the Exclusive`
  line `Economic Zone of any other State including the Exclusive Economic Zone of India;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "other State" means any country other than India;`
  line
  line `(h) "piracy" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any illegal act of violence or detention or any act of depredation committed for private ends`
  line `by any person or by the crew or any passenger of a private ship and directed on the high seas`
  line `against another ship or any person or property on board such ship;`
  line
  line `(ii) any act of voluntary participation in the operation of a ship with knowledge of facts, making`
  line `it a pirate ship;`
  line
  line `(iii) any act of inciting or of intentionally facilitating an act described in sub-clause (i) or`
  line `sub-clause (ii); or`
  line
  line `(iv) any act which is deemed piratical under the international law including customary`
  line `international law;`
  line
  line `(i) "pirate ship" means a ship which---`
  line
  line `(i) is intended by the person in dominant control to be used for the purposes of committing any`
  line `of the acts referred to in sub-clauses (i) to (iv) of clause (h); or`
  line
  line `(ii) has been used to commit any such act, referred to in sub-clause (i) of this clause, so long as`
  line `it remains under the control of the person guilty of that act;`
  line
  line `(j) "ship" means---`
  line
  line `(i) vessel or water craft of every description, including non-displacement craft;`
  line
  line `(ii) sea planes and other aircraft,`
  line
  line `used or capable of being used as means of transportation on water or engaged in any operations at sea.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, aircraft shall have the same meaning as assigned`
  line `to it in clause (1) of section 2 of the Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(k) "stateless person" means a person who is not considered as a national by any country by virtue`
  line `of its laws.`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used in this Act and not defined but defined in the Convention, the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the Code or the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive`
  line `Economic Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), shall have the meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them in such Convention, the Codes or the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (78365)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Punishment for piracy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78365&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Whoever commits any act of piracy, shall be punished--`
  line
  line `(i) with imprisonment which may extend to imprisonment for life or with fine or with both; or`
  line
  line `(ii) with death or with imprisonment for life, if such person in committing the act of piracy causes`
  line `death or an attempt thereof,`
  line
  line `and in addition shall also be subject to restitution or forfeiture of property involved in the commission of`
  line `such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (78366)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Punishment for attempt to commit piracy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78366&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Whoever attempts to commit the offence of`
  line `piracy or aids or abets or conspires or procures for the commission of such offence shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (78367)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Punishment for organising or directing others to participate in an act of piracy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78367&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `participates or organises or directs other person to participate in an act of piracy shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (78368)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Conferment of power of arrest, investigation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78368&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code, the Central Government may, for the purposes of this Act, by notification, confer the powers of`
  line `arrest, investigation and prosecution of any person exercisable by a police officer under the Code on any`
  line `of its officer or such officer of a State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (78369)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Arrest of persons and seizure of ship and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78369&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorised personnel may, either`
  line `generally or on suspicion that a ship is engaged in piracy on the high seas, board such ship and arrest the`
  line `persons or seize the pirate ship and property on board.`
  line
  line `(2) The ship or property seized under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of only by the order of the`
  line court.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (78370)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78370&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of providing speedy trial of offences under this Act, the`
  line `Central Government shall, after consulting the Chief Justice of the concerned High Court, by notification,`
  line specify--
  line
  line `(i) one or more Courts of Sessions in a State, to be the Designated Court for the purposes of this`
  line `Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the territorial jurisdiction of each such court:`
  line
  line `Provided that such territorial jurisdiction shall be determined on the basis of the port or place of`
  line `disembarkation within India of the person suspected or accused of an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (78371)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Jurisdiction of Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78371&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Designated Court shall have jurisdiction to try an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act where such offence is committed--`
  line
  line `(i) by a person who is apprehended by, or is in the custody of, the authorized personnel or the`
  line `police, regardless of the nationality or citizenship of such person;`
  line
  line `(ii) by a person who is a citizen of India or a resident foreign national in India or any stateless`
  line `person:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to a warship or its auxiliary ship or a Government`
  line `owned ship employed for non-commercial service and is under the control of Government authorities`
  line `at the time of commission of the offence of piracy.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (78372)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Trial of offences by Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78372&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code,--`
  line
  line `(a) all offences under this Act shall be tried by the Designated Court notified as such under`
  line `clause (i) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) where a person accused of, or suspected of, the commission of an offence under this Act is`
  line `forwarded to a Magistrate under sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) of section 167 of the Code, such`
  line `Magistrate may authorise the detention of such person in such custody, as he thinks fit, for a period`
  line `not exceeding fifteen days in the whole, where such Magistrate is a Judicial Magistrate, and seven`
  line `days in the whole where such Magistrate is an Executive Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such Magistrate considers--`
  line
  line `(i) at the time when such person is forwarded to him under this sub-section; or`
  line
  line `(ii) at any time before the expiry of the period of detention authorised by him,`
  line
  line `that the detention of such person is not necessary, he shall order such person to be forwarded to the`
  line `Designated Court having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The Designated Court may exercise, in relation to the person forwarded to him under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1), the same power which a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try a case may exercise under`
  line `section 167 of the Code, in relation to an accused person in such case who has been forwarded to him`
  line `under that section.`
  line
  line `(3) A Designated Court may, upon a perusal of a complaint made by an officer of the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, authorised in this behalf, take cognizance of`
  line `that offence without the accused being committed to it for trial.`
  line
  line `(4) While trying an offence under this Act, a Designated Court may also try an offence under any`
  line `other law, other than an offence under this Act, with which the accused may be charged at the same trial`
  line `under the Code.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, a Designated Court shall, as far as practicable,`
  line `hold the trial on a day-to-day basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (78373)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Presumption.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78373&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where a person is accused of having committed an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act and, if,--`
  line
  line `(a) the arms, ammunitions, explosives and other equipments are recovered from the possession of`
  line `the accused, and there are reasonable grounds to believe that such arms, ammunitions, explosives or`
  line `other equipments of similar nature were used or intended to be used in the commission of the offence;`
  line
  line `(b) there is evidence of use of force, threat of force or any other form of intimidation caused to the`
  line `crew or passengers of the ship in connection with the commission of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) there is evidence of an intended threat of using bombs, arms, firearms, explosives or`
  line `committing any form of violence against the crew, passengers or cargo of a ship,`
  line
  line `then, the Designated Court shall presume, unless the contrary is proved, that the accused person had`
  line `committed such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (78374)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provisions as to bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78374&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, no person accused`
  line `of an offence punishable under this Act shall, if in custody, be released on bail or on his own bond`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(a) the Public Prosecutor has been given a reasonable opportunity to oppose the application for`
  line `such release; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the Court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding grant of bail under section 439 of the Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (78375)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Application of Code in proceedings before Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78375&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Act, the provisions of the Code shall apply to the proceedings before a Designated Court and the`
  line `person conducting a prosecution before a Designated Court shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor`
  line `appointed under the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (78376)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provision as to extradition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78376&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The offences under this Act shall be deemed to have been`
  line `included as extraditable offences and provided for in all extradition treaties made by India with any other`
  line `State and which extend to and are binding on India on the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of a bilateral extradition treaty, the offences under this Act shall be extraditable`
  line `offences between India and other State on the basis of reciprocity.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of application of the provisions of the Extradition Act, 1962 (34 of 1962) to the`
  line `offences under this Act, any ship registered in other State shall, at any time while that ship is operating,`
  line `be deemed to be within the jurisdiction of that other State whether or not it is for the time being also`
  line `within the jurisdiction of any other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (78377)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167&sectionId=78377&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_202303_1696834013167
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against an authorised personnel for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government for any damage caused or likely to be caused for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
